name: Sargfabrik
description: Innovative housing project and cultural center built on site of former coffin factory in 14th district. Features cultural venue with alternative touch, restaurant, kindergarten, seminar rooms, and public bathhouse. Hosts concerts, theater and cultural events.

name: Scotch Club
description: Club and bar at Parkring in first district. Note: Official website indicates closure ('Wir haben geschlossen') - verify current status before visiting.

name: Susi
description: Pub and bar near Messe-Prater metro station. Open evenings with food, beer, wine, and hard liquor. Features dine-in service and accepts credit cards.

name: Szene Wien
description: Legendary well-established club in Simmering for over 25 years with 450 capacity. Features various music genres including Alternative, Indie, Rock/Pop, Blues, Folk, Avantgarde, Experimental, plus cabaret and theater. Indoor and outdoor bars with garden.

name: Tanzcafé Jenseits
description: Small bar with legendary status in Sixth district featuring red brocade walls. Hosts cultural events, readings and daily changing DJ line-up. Music ranges from jazz, funk, soul to dance music on weekends. Very cozy atmosphere.

name: The Circus
description: Austria's biggest Gay Party celebrating 14+ years of unforgettable nights. Features international star DJs, sexy GoGo Boys and sassy Drag Queens with spectacular stage productions. Usually at Arena venue, larger events at Prater DOME. Physical shop in 7th district.

name: The Flag
description: Note: No specific venue found with this name in Vienna. This may be a former venue, alternate name, or require verification. Vienna's main LGBTQ+ venues include Felixx, Village Bar, Why Not, Mango Bar, and Sling.

name: The Hive
description: New gay bar and meeting place in Viennese LGBTQ+ scene since July 2020. Welcomes all LGBTQ+ community members with lively, friendly atmosphere. Features cocktails, food, indoor and outdoor seating. Saturday club nights.

name: The Loft
description: Club in former wooden floor factory near U6 Thaliastrasse, opened 2009. Offers entertainment on several levels: café, cozy bar, and dance floor in basement. Part of Vienna's Gürtel nightlife scene.

name: The Tube
description: British Sports Bar owned by Barry Stevens in Landstraße (3rd district). Features three screens showing Football, Rugby, Cricket, Tennis, Darts via SKY Sports, Eurosport, Sport1, DAZN, BT Sports and BBC. Serves British and international beers, bar snacks. Cash only.
